cs.VLSI, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.VLSI - The paper proposes a new design for logic gates using transistor threshold voltage-defined switches, which is a topic related to VLSI design. 
2. cs.CR - The paper discusses security attacks on semiconductor supply chain and proposes a solution to resist against reverse engineering and IP piracy, which falls under the category of computer security. 
3. cs.SE - The proposed gate can also be used to personalize the design during manufacturing, which is related to software engineering. 
4. cs.AR - The paper discusses the physical and logical camouflage of the gate, which is related to augmented reality and virtual reality. 
5. cs.CE - The proposed gate operates at nominal voltage and obeys conventional reliability limits, which is related to computer engineering.
